		Bestiary: {
			Dementor: Among the foulest creatures to walk this earth. They drain peace, hope, and happiness from everything around them. Only a Patronus can repel them.
			Acromantula: A giant spider of immense intelligence and terrifying size. They were first bred by wizards, likely as guard creatures for dwellings or treasure stores.
			MagicPixie: Electric-blue mischief-makers that delight in chaos. Small but deceptively strong, capable of lifting and carrying heavy objects.
			Troll: A fearsome creature standing twelve feet tall with dull, granite-gray skin. Mountain trolls are the largest and most vicious of their kind.
			Inferius: A corpse reanimated by dark magic. They feel no pain and fear only fire. Used as puppet soldiers by the darkest of wizards.
			Basilisk: The King of Serpents. Born from a chicken's egg hatched beneath a toad. Its gaze is fatal, and its venom destroys everything except phoenix tears.
			Horntail: The most dangerous of all dragon breeds. It has bronze horns and a tail covered in spikes. Its fire can reach distances of forty feet.
			Voldemort: The most feared Dark Wizard of all time. Born Tom Marvolo Riddle, he split his soul into fragments to cheat death. Only the united Deathly Hallows can truly end him.
			Thestral: Visible only to those who have witnessed death, these skeletal winged horses are gentle despite their fearsome appearance. They are attracted to the smell of blood.
			DeathEater: A follower of the Dark Lord, marked with the Dark Mark. They practice the darkest of magic and answer only to their master's call.
			Ollivander: A master wandmaker whose family has been crafting fine wands since 382 B.C. He believes the wand chooses the wizard.
			Hagrid: A half-giant with a heart of gold and an unfortunate fondness for dangerous creatures. Now serves as a keeper of magical beasts.
			PotionsMaster: A brilliant but temperamental potioneer. Demands perfection in the art of brewing and has little patience for incompetence.
			Dobby: A free house-elf who delights in helping wizards. Give him a sock and he'll be your friend forever. Known for his collection of mismatched socks and fierce loyalty.
			Lupin: Remus Lupin -- one of the original Marauders and a former Defense Against the Dark Arts professor. A werewolf who bears his affliction with quiet dignity. His deep knowledge of Hogwarts' secret passages makes him an invaluable ally.
			MadamHooch: Hogwarts' flying instructor and Quidditch referee. With hawk-like yellow eyes and decades of experience, she ensures every match is played fairly and every student learns to fly safely.
			Kingsley: Kingsley Shacklebolt -- senior Auror and Order of the Phoenix member. Calm, competent, and deeply trusted by Dumbledore. Serves as the Order's liaison for Ministry-related operations.
			GoblinTeller: A Gringotts bank teller -- sharp-eyed, sharp-tongued, and absolutely precise about gold. Goblins run the wizarding world's only bank with centuries of accumulated expertise and a healthy distrust of wand-carriers.
			MadamRosmerta: The beloved innkeeper of the Three Broomsticks tavern in Hogsmeade. She stocks Honeydukes sweets alongside her famous Butterbeer, making her pub the social anchor of the village and the go-to contact for Owl Post deliveries.
			Mandrake: A magical plant with a root that looks like a small, muddy baby. Its cry is fatal to anyone who hears it at full maturity, though young Mandrakes will merely knock you unconscious.
			Boggart: A shape-shifting creature that takes on the form of whatever most frightens the person nearest to it. Nobody knows what a Boggart looks like when it is alone. Riddikulus!
			Dumbledore: A sentient portrait of the late Albus Dumbledore, greatest Headmaster Hogwarts ever knew. Like all Hogwarts headmaster portraits, it retains his wisdom, personality, and counsel — though it is a reflection, not the man himself. The portrait continues to guide those who seek his advice.
			Werewolf: A wizard or witch afflicted with lycanthropy. Under the full moon they transform into savage beasts. The Wolfsbane Potion allows them to keep their mind during transformation.
			Grindylow: A small, horned water demon with long, brittle fingers. They inhabit lakes and are particularly aggressive toward humans who enter their territory.
			Doxy: A small fairy-like creature covered in thick black hair, with an extra pair of arms and legs. Its venomous bite requires an antidote. They infest curtains and old houses.
			Peeves: The most notorious poltergeist in history. He delights in chaos, pranks, and driving people mad. The only ones he ever listened to were Dumbledore and the Bloody Baron.
			Nagini: The Dark Lord's most faithful companion and final Horcrux. A massive magical serpent of unknown breed, capable of assuming human form. Her venom keeps Voldemort's mortal shell alive.
			Obscurus: A dark parasitic magical force that develops inside a witch or wizard who suppresses their magic. When released, it becomes an uncontrollable destructive entity of immense power. Few Obscurials survive past childhood.
			Aberforth: Aberforth Dumbledore -- younger brother of Albus and keeper of the Hog's Head Inn in Hogsmeade. A gruff, private man who quietly aids the resistance from behind his bar. His Patronus is a goat.
			PrisonWraith: Spectral remains of condemned prisoners who perished within Azkaban's walls. Their despair lingers as ghostly echoes that haunt anyone who disturbs the prison's wards. [Mod-original content]
			DespairAnchor: A corrupted ward anchor from Azkaban's ancient defenses. Once designed to contain prisoners, now it radiates despair to all nearby. Destroying these weakens the dark forces during an Azkaban event. [Mod-original content]
			Bowtruckle: A tree-guardian creature, no taller than eight inches, made of bark and twigs with two small brown eyes. Peaceful unless its home tree is threatened, when it will gouge at eyes with its sharp fingers.
			Flobberworm: The most boring creature in the wizarding world. A thick brown worm that eats lettuce. Its mucus is sometimes used to thicken potions, which is its only known use.
			BlastEndedSkrewt: A horrifying crossbreed of Manticores and Fire Crabs, created by Hagrid. Ten feet long when fully grown, with an armored shell, a powerful stinger, and a blast of fire from its rear end.
			Centaur: A proud and noble creature with the upper body of a human and the lower body of a horse. They are gifted stargazers and consider most human magic beneath them. Do not call them half-breeds.
			AzkabanGuard: An elite Dementor assigned to guard the wizard prison of Azkaban. Larger and far more powerful than its lesser kin, its mere presence extinguishes all light and warmth. Its kiss does not merely feed — it devours the soul entirely.
			Merfolk: The merpeople of the wizarding world dwell in the depths of lakes and oceans. They speak Mermish, a language that sounds like screeching above water. Fierce guardians of their underwater realm, they do not welcome trespassers.
			Sphinx: An ancient creature with the body of a lion, the wings of an eagle, and the head of a human. Sphinxes are highly intelligent and fond of riddles, puzzles, and enigmas. They make excellent guardians of treasure and secret places.
			Giant: Standing twenty feet tall or more, giants are among the most feared creatures in the wizarding world. Though not especially intelligent, their raw strength is unmatched. Some were recruited by Voldemort for the Battle of Hogwarts.
			Fwooper: A brightly coloured African magical bird whose song will drive the listener insane. Fwooper owners are required to place a Silencing Charm on their bird. Comes in vivid pink, lime green, orange, and mustard yellow.
			SnowWraith: A frozen spirit of a long-dead northern wizard. Found in snow biomes at night, they bring an unnatural chill that freezes everything they touch. Rumored to be the ghosts of Durmstrang students who perished in the cold.
			MrBorgin: The oily proprietor of Borgin and Burkes, Knockturn Alley's most notorious shop of dark artefacts. Suspicious, transactional, and profoundly self-interested. He knows the value of every cursed object in his inventory.
			CursedMummy: An ancient Egyptian wizard whose body was cursed to guard their tomb for eternity. The dark magic that preserves them has only grown stronger over millennia. Bill Weasley would know how to handle these.
			FredAndGeorge: The legendary Weasley twins, founders of Weasleys' Wizard Wheezes. Inventors, pranksters, and surprisingly gifted wizards. Their shop in Diagon Alley is the most colorful — and most dangerous — place to shop.
			TrollBoss: A fully grown mountain troll, twelve feet tall with dull grey skin and a massive wooden club. Not bright, but devastating in close quarters. A classic first encounter for any young wizard.
			AragogBoss: Patriarch of the Acromantula colony in the Forbidden Forest. Raised from an egg by Hagrid, Aragog commands an army of his children. When he calls, the spiders come.
			FluffyBoss: A massive three-headed dog placed by Dumbledore to guard the trapdoor. Each head attacks independently. The only way past is music — or brute force.
			BellatrixBoss: The most dangerous and devoted of Voldemort's Death Eaters. Bellatrix Lestrange is a dueling prodigy who delights in cruelty. She killed Sirius Black, tortured the Longbottoms, and fears nothing but her master's displeasure.
			FenrirBoss: The most savage werewolf alive. Fenrir Greyback positions himself near victims at the full moon, driven by a desire to bite and contaminate as many people as possible. He especially targets children.
			DementorKingBoss: Azkaban's Despair — an ancient being of pure darkness that commands legions of soul-sucking wraiths. Its presence extinguishes all light and hope. Only the strongest Patronus can stand against it.
			PhantomStag: A spectral mockery of a true Patronus, twisted by the Hallow's wild magic. Not a real Patronus — a magical echo corrupted by overcharged positive energy. A fully original creature born of the Hallow's excess.
			CursedSpecter: The ghost of a wizard who delved too deep into dark magic and was consumed by the Corruption. Trapped between life and death, it fires cursed flames at any living creature that crosses its path.
			Thunderbird: A massive magical bird native to Arizona, closely related to the phoenix. It can create storms as it flies and sense danger before it arrives. Found wherever storms gather in the sky.
			GoblinRebel: A rogue goblin from the great goblin rebellions of wizarding history. Armed with enchanted Gringotts gold that they weaponize as projectiles. They carry significant wealth — if you can take it from them.
			Lethifold: Also known as the Living Shroud, one of the most dangerous creatures in the magical world. It resembles a black cloak that glides along the ground, smothering sleeping victims. Only a Patronus Charm can repel it.
			QuirrellBoss: A stuttering professor of Defence Against the Dark Arts with a terrible secret. Beneath his turban lurks the face of the Dark Lord himself, sharing Quirrell's body as a parasitic host. What begins as a simple duel becomes a fight for survival when Voldemort reveals himself.
			UmbridgeBoss: Senior Undersecretary to the Minister for Magic and the most hated woman in the wizarding world. She doesn't fight with raw power — she fights with bureaucracy, debuffs, and Educational Decrees. The only boss that makes you WISH for Voldemort instead.
			BartyCrouchBoss: A Death Eater so dedicated he escaped Azkaban and spent a year disguised as Mad-Eye Moody using Polyjuice Potion. His true form is just as dangerous as his disguise — a master duelist who served the Dark Lord with fanatical loyalty.
			Erumpent: A massive creature resembling a rhinoceros, native to Africa. Its horn contains a deadly fluid that causes whatever it is injected into to explode. Erumpent horns, tails, and exploding fluid are all Class B Tradeable Materials.
			Occamy: A plumed, serpentine creature with wings, native to the Far East and India. It is choranaptyxic — meaning it grows or shrinks to fit available space. Its eggs are made of the purest, softest silver.
			Zouwu: An enormous magical feline beast, as big as an elephant, with a multicoloured mane and a body that can grow or shrink at will. Incredibly fast and powerful — it can travel a thousand miles in a day. Native to China.
			Demiguise: A peaceful, ape-like creature with large, soulful eyes and long, silky, silvery hair. It can make itself invisible when threatened, which makes it extremely hard to catch. Its pelts are used for ordinary invisibility cloaks and concealment gear — not the unique Deathly Hallow.
			Mooncalf: A shy creature that emerges only at night during a full moon. Mooncalves perform complicated dances on their hind legs in the moonlight, which creates intricate geometric patterns in wheat fields. Their silvery dung, if collected before sunrise, makes magical plants grow extraordinarily fast.
			Billywig: A tiny sapphire-blue insect native to Australia. Its sting causes giddiness followed by levitation. Dried Billywig stings are used as an ingredient in Fizzing Whizzbees. The insect is incredibly fast and rarely seen by Muggles.
			Ashwinder: A thin, pale grey serpent with glowing red eyes that is born from the embers of a magical fire left to burn unchecked. It lives for only an hour, seeking a dark, secluded spot to lay its eggs before crumbling to dust. The eggs are intensely hot and will ignite dwellings within minutes if not frozen.
			Nundu: A gigantic magical leopard native to East Africa and considered the most dangerous living creature in the wizarding world. Its breath is toxic and can decimate entire villages. It has never been subdued by fewer than a hundred wizards working together.
			Runespoor: A three-headed serpent commonly reaching six to seven feet in length. The left head is the planner, the middle head is the dreamer, and the right head is the critic. Native to Burkina Faso. Its eggs are valuable in potion-making.
			Jarvey: A magical creature that resembles an overgrown ferret, except that it can talk. Unfortunately, a Jarvey is incapable of true conversation and confines itself to short, usually rude, phrases in an almost constant stream. Found in Britain, Ireland, and North America.
			FireCrab: Despite its name, the Fire Crab resembles a large tortoise with a heavily jewelled shell. It is found on the coast of Fiji and exports are strictly controlled. The Fire Crab's chief defence is shooting flames from its rear end when attacked.
			Puffskein: A round, custard-coloured creature covered in soft fur. It is a docile, even cuddly creature that has no objection to being tossed around or cuddled. It hums when content. A popular wizard pet and the ancestor of the Pygmy Puff.
			Streeler: A giant snail that changes colour on an hourly basis. It leaves behind a trail of venomous slime so toxic it shrivels and burns all vegetation it touches. The Streeler is kept as a pet by those who enjoy its kaleidoscopic colour changes.
			PeruvianVipertooth: The smallest of all known dragons, reaching only fifteen feet in length. Its scales are smooth and copper-coloured, with a distinctive black ridge marking. It has venomous fangs and is particularly fast, making it exceptionally dangerous despite its size.
			Diricawl: A plump, fluffy, flightless bird with the remarkable ability to vanish in a puff of feathers when threatened. Muggles once knew it as the Dodo and believe they drove it to extinction — unaware that it simply teleported away.
			Knarl: Resembles a hedgehog so closely that there is only one known difference: if you leave food out for a hedgehog, it will appreciate it. A Knarl will assume you are trying to lure it into a trap and savage your garden.
			Horklump: A fleshy, pink, mushroom-like creature. It is difficult to distinguish from a mushroom, which is just as well since it does nothing at all besides spread itself. The only known use for a Horklump is as Flobberworm food.
			Jobberknoll: A tiny blue speckled bird that makes absolutely no sound until the moment of its death, at which point it lets out a long scream consisting of every sound it has ever heard, regurgitated backwards. Jobberknoll feathers are used in Truth Serums and Memory Potions.
			Dugbog: A marsh-dwelling creature that resembles a dead piece of wood while stationary. When an unsuspecting creature or person walks past, the Dugbog lunges with its toothed maw. It feeds mainly on Mandrakes and has been known to bite the ankles of humans.
			MagicalImp: A tiny mischievous creature made of living flame. Imps are not especially dangerous individually, but they spawn in swarms in hot environments. They delight in starting small fires and throwing fireballs at passersby.
		}

		GreatHall: {
