		Dialogue: {
			Ollivander: {
				Standard1: "Curious... very curious. The wand chooses the wizard, you know."
				Standard2: "I remember every wand I've ever sold. Every single wand."
				Standard3: "Try this one. Unicorn hair core, eleven inches. Give it a wave!"
				Standard4: "The wand of yew is among the rarer kinds, and their ideal matches are likewise unusual."
				Standard5: "Dragon heartstring wands learn more quickly than others, but can be prone to accidents."
				Standard6: "Unicorn hair cores are the most faithful, though they rarely produce the strongest magic."
				Standard7: "Have you tried the Enchanting Table? It's where all the finest wands are crafted these days."
				Rare: "He Who Must Not Be Named did great things... terrible, yes, but great."
				PostVoldemort: "The Elder Wand has chosen you. I never thought I'd see the day..."
				PostBasilisk: "You defeated the Basilisk? With THAT wand? Remarkable. Perhaps you're ready for something stronger."
				Hardmode: "The world has changed. Darker creatures roam now. You'll need more powerful wands. Have a look."
			}
			Hagrid: {
				Standard1: "I shouldn't have told yer that. I should NOT have told yer that."
				Standard2: "There's no place safer than right here, I reckon."
				Standard3: "Yer a wizard! Well... close enough."
				Standard4: "Beautifully misunderstood creatures, really. Dragons, I mean."
				Standard5: "Norbert? Norberta? Ah, don't remind me..."
				Standard6: "The Forbidden Forest ain't for the faint of heart, but there's beauties in there too."
				Standard7: "I've got some lovely Flobberworms out back if yer interested. No? Suit yerself."
				Rare: "I'd trust Dumbledore with me life, I would."
				PostBasilisk: "Yeh did it! The Basilisk is gone. Chamber's safe now, I reckon."
				PostAragog: "Aragog... he was a good friend. But I understand why yeh had to."
				PostHorntail: "A Hungarian Horntail! Blimey, even Charlie would be impressed!"
				PostVoldemort: "He's gone. Really gone this time. Dumbledore would be proud of yeh."
				Night: "Best not wander the forest at night. Not all creatures in there are friendly."
			}
			PotionsMaster: {
				Standard1: "I can teach you how to bottle fame, brew glory, even stopper death."
				Standard2: "Clearly, fame isn't everything. Turn to page 394."
				Standard3: "The art of potion-making requires... subtlety."
				Standard4: "There will be no foolish wand-waving in this shop."
				Standard5: "I see no difference between your last potion and pond water."
				Standard6: "Felix Felicis is extraordinarily tricky to brew. One mistake and the consequences are disastrous."
				Standard7: "If I catch you pocketing ingredients, I shall make you wish you hadn't."
				Rare: "Always."
				SeeFelixBuff: "I see you're under the influence of Felix Felicis. Brewed it yourself, did you? ...Adequate."
				SeeFirewhiskeyBuff: "*sniff* ...Is that Firewhiskey? In MY shop? I should confiscate that. ...But I won't."
				PostVoldemort: "The Dark Lord is gone. I fulfilled my promise. That is all you need to know."
			}
			Dobby: {
				Standard1: "Dobby is a free elf! Dobby can help however sir or madam wishes!"
				Standard2: "Dobby has heard of your greatness, but Dobby never knew..."
				Standard3: "Would sir like a pair of socks? Dobby's favorite clothing article!"
				Standard4: "Dobby has no master! Dobby is a free elf and Dobby has come to help!"
				Standard5: "Dobby will always be there for those who ask for help at Hogwarts."
				Standard6: "Dobby tried to bake a cake once. It... did not go well for the house."
				Standard7: "Dobby likes this place very much. Nobody throws shoes at Dobby here."
				Rare: "Master has given Dobby a sock! Dobby is free!"
				PostVoldemort: "The Dark Lord is gone! Dobby is so happy! Dobby wants to celebrate with socks for everyone!"
				Night: "Dobby does not like the dark. Bad things happen in the dark. But Dobby is brave!"
				PostBasilisk: "The big snake is gone? Dobby remembers the chamber... Dobby is glad it is safe now."
			}
			Dumbledore: {
				Standard1: "It does not do to dwell on dreams and forget to live."
				Standard2: "Happiness can be found even in the darkest of times, if one only remembers to turn on the light."
				Standard3: "It is our choices that show what we truly are, far more than our abilities."
				Standard4: "Words are, in my not-so-humble opinion, our most inexhaustible source of magic."
				Standard5: "Of course it is happening inside your head, but why on earth should that mean that it is not real?"
				Standard6: "To the well-organized mind, death is but the next great adventure."
				Standard7: "Nitwit! Blubber! Oddment! Tweak! ...I do enjoy a good feast."
				Rare: "After all this time? Always."
				PostDementorKing: "You have conquered despair itself. There is no greater victory than hope prevailing over darkness."
				BloodMoon: "Even the moon bleeds tonight. Stay vigilant — dark creatures grow bold under crimson light."
				HighMana: "I sense great magical power within you. Use it wisely — power is neither good nor evil, only the wielder decides."
			}
			Centaur: {
				Standard1: "Mars is bright tonight. There will be conflict."
				Standard2: "We observe, we do not interfere. Usually."
				Standard3: "The stars do not lie. But they are often misinterpreted."
				Standard4: "Humans are so hasty. The planets move in centuries, not minutes."
				Standard5: "Venus is in retrograde. I would not craft anything important today."
				Standard6: "The centaurs of this forest have watched many ages pass. We remember what others forget."
				Standard7: "You walk with purpose. The stars say you carry a great destiny... or a heavy bag."
				Rare: "I have seen things in the stars that trouble me greatly, human."
				FullMoon: "The full moon reveals all truths. Tonight, the stars speak clearly — something ancient stirs."
				NewMoon: "The new moon hides much. Even the stars are uncertain tonight. Tread carefully."
				BloodMoon: "Mars burns with fury! The blood moon is upon us — the darkest creatures will hunt tonight. Stay armed."
			}
			MadamHooch: {
				Standard1: "Everyone on their brooms, please! And do try not to fall off this time."
				Standard2: "I've been refereeing Quidditch at Hogwarts for longer than most of you have been alive."
				Standard3: "A good broom is worth every Galleon. Keep yours well-polished."
				Standard4: "The Quidditch Cup is what makes Hogwarts truly alive, if you ask me."
				Season: "The season is heating up! Make sure you're practicing your Quaffle throws."
				CupWon: "What a season that was! I haven't seen flying like that in years."
			}
			Kingsley: {
				Standard1: The Order is always watching. Dark times call for constant vigilance.
				Standard2: I work undercover at the Ministry. Trust no one you haven't tested.
				Standard3: Dumbledore's network runs deeper than most realize.
				Standard4: The Department of Mysteries holds secrets worth protecting.
				Veteran: You've proven yourself in the field. The Order is grateful.
				Night: The Order keeps watch through the night. Darkness is no stranger to us.
				Grimmauld: Number Twelve needs maintenance. The wards weaken if the safehouse is neglected.
			}
			GoblinTeller: {
				Standard1: Time is Galleons, wizard. State your business.
				Standard2: Gringotts has stood for centuries. We intend to keep it that way.
				Standard3: Touch nothing that is not yours. The vaults remember.
				Standard4: The deeper the vault, the stronger the wards. You have been warned.
				Returning: Back again? Your contract record is satisfactory. Proceed.
			}
			MadamRosmerta: {
				Standard1: "Welcome to the Three Broomsticks! What'll it be — Butterbeer or something stronger?"
				Standard2: "I stock all the best Honeydukes sweets right here at the tavern. Saves you a trip down the lane!"
				Standard3: "Hogsmeade's the heart of the wizarding world, if you ask me. Everyone passes through sooner or later."
				Standard4: "Running an inn means you hear everything. Owls in, owls out — I keep this village connected."
				Standard5: "Honeydukes sends me a fresh crate of Chocolate Frogs every week. They sell faster than Butterbeer some days!"
				Night: "The Three Broomsticks never truly closes. Pull up a chair — nights in Hogsmeade can be long."
				PostVoldemort: "He's gone... I can hardly believe it. The Three Broomsticks will be pouring free Butterbeer all week!"
				OwlPostComplete: "Today's delivery has already been completed. Check back tomorrow!"
				OwlPostSuccess: "Wonderful! The owl has been dispatched with your delivery. Here's your reward!"
				OwlPostButton: Owl Post
			}
			MrBorgin: {
				Standard1: Ah, a customer. Or... are you here on Ministry business? Either way, gold speaks.
				Standard2: I deal in rare and unusual objects. Nothing illegal, of course. Not anymore.
				Standard3: Touch nothing without asking. Some of these items bite back. Literally.
				Standard4: Borgin and Burkes has served discerning wizards for generations. We ask no questions.
				Returning: Back again? Your containment work has been... adequate. There is more to do.
			}
			FredAndGeorge: {
				Standard1: "Step right up! Weasleys' Wizard Wheezes — your one-stop shop for all things magical and mischievous!"
				Standard2: "We've got everything from Skiving Snackboxes to Peruvian Instant Darkness Powder!"
				Standard3: "Mum still doesn't approve, but have you SEEN our sales figures?"
				Standard4: "Give us a bad review and the next Howler's on the house. Literally."
				Standard5: "Try our new Nosebleed Nougat! Trade blood for mana — it's perfectly safe! Mostly."
				Standard6: "The Puking Pastille is our best seller. Nothing clears debuffs faster — or your stomach."
				Standard7: "Skiving Snackbox: when you absolutely MUST fake your own death to avoid a boss attack."
				Standard8: "We once turned an entire corridor into a swamp. Best day of our lives."
				Rare: "We solemnly swear that we are up to no good."
				DuringInvasion: "Death Eaters? BRILLIANT! Time to test our new Shield Hats in ACTUAL combat!"
				PostVoldemort: "You-Know-Who is GONE? This calls for a celebration! Fireworks on the house — literally!"
				PostUmbridge: "You got rid of Umbridge?! We've been wanting to do that for YEARS. Our hero!"
				BloodMoon: "Red moon, red sales! Everything's half-off tonight! ...Okay, not really. But the Nosebleed Nougats are fitting."
			}
			Healer: {
				Standard1: "St Mungo's is always short-staffed. Every wand that can help is welcome."
				Standard2: "Spell damage, creature injuries, potion accidents — we see it all in triage."
				Standard3: "The wards rotate. Each one has its own hazards. Stay alert in there."
				Standard4: "Healer's Salts are distilled from the residue we neutralize. Useful for crafting."
				Veteran: "You've done good work in the wards. The patients owe you a debt."
			}
			Lupin: {
				Standard1: "The trick to Defense Against the Dark Arts is knowing what you're afraid of — and facing it anyway."
				Standard2: "I knew your parents, in a manner of speaking. They were brave people."
				Standard3: "The Marauder's Map never lies. It shows every person, every passage, every secret."
				Standard4: "Chocolate helps after encounters with dark creatures. Trust me on this one."
				FullMoon: "I'm... not feeling entirely myself tonight. Perhaps keep your distance."
				Shack: "The Shrieking Shack holds memories for me. Not all of them pleasant, but important nonetheless."
			}
			Aberforth: {
				Standard1: "The Hog's Head serves everyone. No questions asked. That's how it's always been."
				Standard2: "My brother had his grand plans. I prefer keeping my head down and my bar open."
				Standard3: "Don't trust everything you hear about Albus. He was brilliant, but he wasn't perfect."
				Standard4: "The passage behind the portrait leads to Hogwarts. Use it wisely."
				Standard5: "I've seen dark times before. Survived them all. You will too, if you're clever."
				Resistance: "The D.A. is meeting tonight. The wards need reinforcing -- Hogwarts depends on it."
			}
			Neville: {
				Standard1: "I'm not as brave as people say. I just do what needs doing."
				Standard2: "Gran always said I'd amount to nothing. Proved her wrong, didn't I?"
				Standard3: "The D.A. taught me more than any class ever did. We look after each other."
				Standard4: "Hogwarts is worth fighting for. Every stone, every corridor, every student."
				NaginiDone: "Nagini is gone. That's one less tether holding the Dark Lord to this world."
			}
		}

